manager/errors/`\n- [ ] Define `HTTPError` struct with Code, Message, StatusCode, Details, RequestID fields\n- [ ] Implement `Error()` method for HTTPError\n- [ ] Add JSON tags using camelCase naming\n- [ ] Define error constructor functions: NewNotFoundError, NewValidationError\n- [ ] Define error constructor functions: NewConflictError, NewInternalError, NewTimeoutError\n- [ ] Add service error constants: ErrWorkloadNotFound, ErrWorkloadAlreadyExists\n- [ ] Add service error constants: ErrValidationFailed\n- [ ] Add error mapping function `MapServiceError()` with switch statement\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: Define Request and Response DTOs\n**Verifiable Output:** `pkg/workloadmanager/types/` contains request.go and response.go\n\n- [ ] Create `request.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/`\n- [ ] Define `WorkloadType` string type with constants: WorkloadTypeAgentRuntime, WorkloadTypeCodeInterpreter\n- [ ] Define `CreateWorkloadRequest` struct with Namespace, Name, Type, AgentRuntimeSpec, CodeInterpreterSpec, Labels, Annotations fields\n- [ ] Define `UpdateWorkloadRequest` struct with AgentRuntimeSpec, CodeInterpreterSpec, Labels, Annotations fields\n- [ ] Define `ListWorkloadsRequest` struct with Namespace, Type, LabelSelector, FieldSelector, Limit, Continue fields\n- [ ] Add validation tags using `validate:` struct tags\n- [ ] Create `response.go` in `pkg/workloadmanager/types/`\n- [ ] Define `Response` struct with Success, Data, Error, RequestID, Timestamp fields\n- [ ] Define `ErrorDetail` struct with Code, Message, Details fields\n- [ ] Define `WorkloadResponse` struct with Type, Namespace, Name, UID, CreatedAt, ResourceVersion, Labels, Annotations, Spec, Status fields\n- [ ] Define `ListWorkloadsResponse` struct with Items, Total, Continue, RemainingItemCount fields\n- [ ] Define `HealthResponse` struct with Status, Checks, Version fields\n- [ ] Define `HealthCheck` struct with Status, Message, LastChecked fields\n- [ ] Define `WorkloadEvent` struct with Type, Workload